Redfish Validator pass?
Tested with the Redfish Validator and updated the commit message.
For some reason, some of the cores are reporting 9~11x duplicate of threads (thread 0 appears 10x for example). Strangely, this is not always the case.

Ah, it seems like making the ObjectMapper call that `getCollectionMembers` calls on https://github.com/openbmc/bmcweb/blob/002d39b4a7a5ed7166e2acad84e0943c3def9492/redfish-core/include/utils/collection.hpp#L26

I'm seeing that the corepath that looks like cpu0/core1 will grab cpu0/core10~19 as well... I'm guessing this may be a bug in the getCollectionMembers?

After a discussion with Ed upstream, it seems the problem was actually introduced a while ago in object mapper : https://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-objmgr/commit/153494e0dfb6cbc47ce8506ded4f0fd59f9436c4

We should be "adding" the trailing / instead of removing it, as we do a "starts_with" search
Thanks Brandon, for finding the root cause.
This is fixed with : https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/phosphor-objmgr/+/55196
Please add me to existing and future Agentless changes.
Please don't use this style in new codes. We prefer inline functions instead of local lambdas
These are not local lambdas though. They are being passed as argument. Let me see if I can pass inline function as argument instead and maintain its inline property
Done
